# Enclosure Health LLM Guide

Use this command as the default preflight and post-change verification for repositories with an enclosure contract.

## When To Run

- Before making changes, after reading `.enclosure/` guidance.
- After changes, before summarizing results to the user.
- Whenever you need one command that moves from workspace contract health to architecture health.

## How To Interpret

- Error findings are blocking; name the focused follow-up command in your response.
- Workspace findings point to `enclosure workspace health`, `enclosure workspace rules`, or `enclosure workspace recipe --check`.
- Architecture findings point to `enclosure architecture health`, `enclosure architecture boundaries`, `enclosure architecture shape`, `enclosure architecture map`, or `enclosure architecture clusters`.
- Passing root health does not replace relevant tests; it confirms the enclosure contract and architecture preflight.
